WEBVTT

00:02.550 --> 00:05.589
Packed your favorite... strawberries.

00:05.590 --> 00:08.341
Mom, strawberries aren't
my favorite fruit anymore.

00:08.342 --> 00:09.879
Since when?

00:09.880 --> 00:12.380
Since I had the pleasure
of tasting a tangelo.

00:12.388 --> 00:15.079
Now my top five fruits are, in order,

00:15.080 --> 00:17.659
tangelos, guava, tomatoes...

00:17.660 --> 00:19.129
they're a fruit, Google it...

00:19.130 --> 00:21.230
kiwi, and pluots.

00:22.022 --> 00:23.439
Got to love Westport.

00:23.440 --> 00:25.239
The closest I got to
fresh fruit as a kid

00:25.240 --> 00:27.110
was wild cherry cough drops.

00:32.439 --> 00:33.560
Oh, no!

00:33.570 --> 00:34.979
Principal Ablin's gonna ask me

00:34.980 --> 00:37.620
to chaperone another one of
Anna-Kat's class field trips!

00:37.621 --> 00:41.290
Katie, I need to speak to you

00:41.300 --> 00:46.129
about the field trip tomorrow.

00:46.130 --> 00:47.930
I got to come up with an excuse.

00:47.940 --> 00:49.399
What have I used in the past?

00:49.400 --> 00:51.459
I've done root canal.
I've done malaria twice.

00:51.460 --> 00:53.419
I had my hip replaced
at a very young age.

00:53.420 --> 00:54.680
Wait.

00:54.690 --> 00:56.359
I actually have a legitimate excuse

00:56.360 --> 00:57.599
for not going on the field trip!

00:57.600 --> 00:59.309
Katie, I was wondering if you w...

00:59.310 --> 01:00.839
I can't chaperone the field trip!

01:00.840 --> 01:02.100
I have a job!

01:02.110 --> 01:04.063
Ha! In your face!

01:04.063 --> 01:05.272
Why is it in my face?

01:05.274 --> 01:07.949
I don't know. You figure it
out. You're the educator.

01:10.195 --> 01:13.240
- Synced & corrected by<font color="#E83286"> MementMori </font>-
-- <font color="#138CE9">www.addic7ed.com</font> --

01:19.872 --> 01:20.913
Long day at work?

01:20.914 --> 01:22.999
Long month at work.

01:23.000 --> 01:24.929
I have been working overtime

01:24.930 --> 01:27.545
planning the Founder's Day Fair.

01:27.546 --> 01:29.639
- What's that?
- It is the fair in three weeks

01:29.640 --> 01:31.620
that celebrates the founding
fathers of Westport.

01:32.340 --> 01:35.619
All I know is, I ordered a
gluten-free funnel cake today,

01:35.620 --> 01:37.009
and part of me died.

01:37.010 --> 01:39.319
I could really use a
big-time pony play session

01:39.320 --> 01:40.350
with you right now.

01:40.351 --> 01:41.934
Okay. Choose your filly.

01:41.935 --> 01:44.729
Where's Sir Sparkles?

01:44.730 --> 01:46.750
He died last month saving Sassy Sadie

01:46.760 --> 01:48.419
from drowning in the toilet.

01:48.420 --> 01:50.193
I begged him to learn how to swim.

01:50.194 --> 01:53.089
I don't recognize most of these ponies.

01:53.090 --> 01:55.320
I've gotten a lot of new ones lately.

01:55.330 --> 01:58.300
Here's my favorite... Major Cuddles!

01:58.310 --> 01:59.999
Major isn't just his rank,

02:00.000 --> 02:02.299
but also how I describe his hugs,

02:02.300 --> 02:03.999
because even though he's military,

02:04.000 --> 02:05.792
he's not emotionally distant.

02:05.793 --> 02:08.068
Anna-Kat, I'm sorry

02:08.070 --> 02:10.079
that I've been working
nights and weekends

02:10.080 --> 02:12.109
and haven't been able to
play with you as much.

02:12.110 --> 02:14.279
It's okay, Mom. I know you're busy.

02:14.280 --> 02:16.049
I actually don't expect
you to be around,

02:16.050 --> 02:17.470
so I just assume you won't be.

02:17.471 --> 02:21.379
And the new number-one thing a
mother never wants to hear is...

02:21.380 --> 02:23.289
what Anna-Kat just said.

02:23.290 --> 02:25.319
Till Oliver says, "We're
putting you in a home.

02:25.320 --> 02:26.437
No cable."

02:28.460 --> 02:30.959
Did you know Sir Sparkles died?

02:30.960 --> 02:32.402
Oh, yeah. That was a rough one.

02:32.403 --> 02:33.569
He didn't have a will.

02:33.570 --> 02:35.299
His colts are still
fighting over his estate.

02:35.300 --> 02:37.969
I used to know everything
going on with her.

02:37.970 --> 02:39.409
I feel so disconnected.

02:39.410 --> 02:40.785
Don't be so hard on yourself.

02:40.786 --> 02:42.339
I bet you know all the pony names.

02:42.340 --> 02:43.700
Of course I do. I'm a good parent.

02:44.623 --> 02:46.582
... married to another good parent.

02:46.583 --> 02:47.792
Mm-hmm.

02:47.793 --> 02:49.549
So, here we are...

02:49.550 --> 02:50.629
two good parents.

02:51.720 --> 02:54.380
I'm just having a hard time with
the work/life balance thing.

02:54.383 --> 02:55.990
Look, we're lucky I can
adjust my schedule

02:56.000 --> 02:57.759
and work out of the house
more and be with the kids.

02:57.760 --> 02:58.979
When one of us is busy,

02:58.980 --> 03:00.596
the other can pick up
the slack. We're a team.

03:00.597 --> 03:02.959
I know, but I still feel bad.

03:02.960 --> 03:04.319
Anna-Kat is getting older,

03:04.320 --> 03:06.599
and I don't want our
relationship to become

03:06.600 --> 03:08.059
like my relationship with Taylor.

03:08.060 --> 03:09.599
What's wrong with that?

03:09.600 --> 03:10.869
Taylor, how you doing, honey?

03:10.870 --> 03:12.740
Get off my back, man!

03:14.020 --> 03:15.809
Well, if you want to spend
more time with Anna-Kat,

03:15.810 --> 03:17.947
maybe you should chaperone the
field trip instead of me.

03:17.948 --> 03:18.948
You're chaperoning?

03:18.949 --> 03:20.283
Yeah, Ablin called and asked me to go.

03:20.284 --> 03:23.849
Well, look at you...

03:23.850 --> 03:26.619
knowing pony names,
chaperoning field trips.

03:26.620 --> 03:28.819
Part of the problem is,
you're too nice of a dad.

03:28.820 --> 03:30.042
You need to be worse.

03:30.043 --> 03:31.127
When it comes to parenting,

03:31.128 --> 03:33.004
I don't go up to you...
you come down to me.

03:33.005 --> 03:34.464
Why do I always have
to come down to you?

03:34.465 --> 03:35.929
I don't do self-improvement.

03:35.930 --> 03:37.490
You knew that when you married me, bro.

03:42.740 --> 03:45.057
I don't feel well.

03:45.058 --> 03:46.894
Yeah, right! Go get dressed.

03:46.895 --> 03:48.260
I'm being serious!

03:48.270 --> 03:49.490
I've been throwing up all night.

03:49.500 --> 03:50.810
Why don't you ever believe me?

03:50.814 --> 03:52.523
- 'Cause you always fake being sick.
- Mm-hmm.

03:52.524 --> 03:53.983
You're thinking of Mom and malaria.

03:53.984 --> 03:55.229
I do do that.

03:55.230 --> 03:57.300
I swear... I'm really sick.

03:57.920 --> 03:59.160
Trip is going to Thunder Park

03:59.170 --> 04:00.698
for senior ditch day, and I want to go.

04:00.699 --> 04:01.783
So fake being sick.

04:01.784 --> 04:03.819
I fake being sick way too many times.

04:03.820 --> 04:05.453
Unless I barf up some arthritis...

04:05.454 --> 04:07.399
- That's not a thing.
- ... then Mom and Dad won't buy it.

04:07.400 --> 04:08.414
I need your help.

04:10.800 --> 04:12.999
They might not buy you being sick,

04:13.000 --> 04:14.599
but they will if we both are sick.

04:14.600 --> 04:15.879
Wait... you're sick?

04:15.880 --> 04:17.539
That's great! Then you can get me sick!

04:17.540 --> 04:18.639
Quick... sneeze in my mouth.

04:18.640 --> 04:21.379
No! I'll also fake being sick.

04:21.380 --> 04:22.389
Oh.

04:22.390 --> 04:24.509
They'll never think we're both lying.

04:24.510 --> 04:25.659
But if I do this for you,

04:25.660 --> 04:27.892
you guys need to take me and
Cooper to Thunder Park.

04:27.893 --> 04:29.249
Fine.

04:29.250 --> 04:30.269
What's the plan?

04:32.650 --> 04:34.190
I've been throwing up all night.

04:34.191 --> 04:35.733
Oh, no. Taylor, too.

04:35.734 --> 04:36.859
Geez, if they're both sick,

04:36.860 --> 04:38.770
then maybe Taylor is
not lying after all.

04:38.779 --> 04:40.019
Maybe they have food poisoning.

04:41.020 --> 04:42.719
Just follow my lead.

04:42.720 --> 04:43.741
Hey, Mom?

04:43.742 --> 04:45.519
Can I have this yogurt smoothie

04:45.520 --> 04:46.530
I found in the fridge?

04:46.537 --> 04:47.539
Sure.

04:47.540 --> 04:49.413
Great. It looks delicious.

04:49.414 --> 04:51.159
Hey, Taylor, you want to share

04:51.160 --> 04:53.009
this yogurt smoothie I
found in the fridge?

04:53.010 --> 04:54.168
It looks delicious.

04:54.169 --> 04:56.213
Sure. It looks delicious.

04:57.840 --> 04:59.959
Oh, no! It's expired.

04:59.960 --> 05:01.419
Oh, who cares?

05:01.420 --> 05:03.539
Mom always said it's
okay to eat expired food

05:03.540 --> 05:05.010
if it's in the two-week buffer zone.

05:05.640 --> 05:07.720
Oh, well. Bottoms up.

05:08.150 --> 05:10.893
You guys are total idiots for
drinking that expired smoothie.

05:10.894 --> 05:12.228
But it was in the buffer zone!

05:12.229 --> 05:13.688
- Did you smell it?
- No.

05:13.689 --> 05:15.529
Everyone knows you got to smell it

05:15.530 --> 05:16.959
if it's in the buffer zone.

05:16.960 --> 05:18.700
That is buffer zone 101.

05:18.710 --> 05:20.403
Back to bed. No school
for you two today.

05:20.404 --> 05:22.220
I'm sorry I can't stay
and take care of them.

05:22.280 --> 05:23.529
I have to go on Anna-Kat's field trip.

05:23.530 --> 05:24.560
Oh, don't worry, Dad.

05:24.570 --> 05:26.019
Oliver and I can take
care of each other.

05:26.020 --> 05:27.029
That's sweet.

05:27.030 --> 05:29.078
Stop being the nice parent.
You're making me look bad.

05:29.079 --> 05:30.454
You could try being the nice parent.

05:30.455 --> 05:31.809
We can't change it up now, Greg.

05:31.810 --> 05:34.009
- We are in this way too deep.
- Hmm.

05:35.480 --> 05:38.749
I need some advice on
what to do with Anna-Kat.

05:38.750 --> 05:40.280
I don't have time to do the fun stuff

05:40.290 --> 05:42.519
that we usually do
together because of work.

05:42.520 --> 05:44.385
Oh. I can totally relate to that.

05:44.386 --> 05:46.229
- Really?
- That's not possible.

05:46.230 --> 05:47.930
Recently, I started spending

05:47.940 --> 05:49.099
more time at home with the kids,

05:49.100 --> 05:50.799
but then I felt like I was missing out

05:50.800 --> 05:52.436
on all this fun stuff
at the country club.

05:52.437 --> 05:54.200
I felt bad for neglecting the club,

05:54.210 --> 05:56.240
so I started spending less time at home.

05:57.316 --> 05:58.566
Hmm.

05:58.567 --> 06:00.590
Katie, if you want to spend
time with your kids,

06:00.600 --> 06:02.409
then sometimes that means
doing things with them

06:02.410 --> 06:04.196
that you don't want to
do... like chaperoning.

06:04.197 --> 06:05.879
But I already did that last year.

06:05.880 --> 06:08.951
Yeah, well, it's kind of like
the mammogram of parenting.

06:08.952 --> 06:11.879
Ugh. Just another way they
put the squeeze on us!

06:11.880 --> 06:13.719
I don't want to chaperone again.

06:13.720 --> 06:15.060
It was just a lot of me saying,

06:15.070 --> 06:16.759
"Don't wander off! Stay together!

06:16.760 --> 06:17.769
Don't climb on that!"

06:17.770 --> 06:19.059
"Don't tell your mom I hit you."

06:19.060 --> 06:21.159
But I did have fun with Anna-Kat.

06:21.160 --> 06:23.749
We sang songs on the bus,
and we made up this game

06:23.750 --> 06:25.149
where we pretended not to know anything

06:25.150 --> 06:26.969
because it was our first day on Earth.

06:26.970 --> 06:28.769
- Example, please.
- Mm.

06:28.770 --> 06:31.339
"What is this mysterious
brown substance?"

06:31.340 --> 06:32.760
Yeah, I don't care anymore.

06:32.770 --> 06:34.539
Katie, there's no
reason why you can't go

06:34.540 --> 06:36.605
on that field trip today and
reconnect with Anna-Kat.

06:36.606 --> 06:38.139
You're right.

06:38.140 --> 06:39.690
- I'm gonna do it.
- Great.

06:39.691 --> 06:40.776
When do they leave?

06:40.777 --> 06:42.359
10 minutes.

06:42.360 --> 06:44.380
- Damn! I got to go.
- Oh.

06:45.280 --> 06:47.360
You didn't really hit a kid
on a field trip, did you?

06:47.366 --> 06:48.519
Oh.

06:48.520 --> 06:49.640
Your son didn't tell you?

06:49.680 --> 06:52.929
Damn, you're a good mom!
You didn't raise a narc!

06:58.660 --> 06:59.729
All right, kids.

06:59.730 --> 07:02.169
Everyone take your seats. We're leaving.

