07:17.521 --> 07:19.959
Good morning, room 5!

07:19.960 --> 07:22.020
My name is Katie Otto, Anna-Kat's mom,

07:22.025 --> 07:24.289
and I am here to chaperone
your field trip

07:24.290 --> 07:25.859
to Caldwell Farms.

07:25.860 --> 07:26.869
Katie, what are you doing here?

07:26.870 --> 07:28.199
I think my announcement one second ago

07:28.200 --> 07:29.400
was pretty clear about that.

07:29.408 --> 07:31.459
Yeah, but I took the day
off from work to...

07:38.760 --> 07:40.719
What are you doing here?
I thought you had a job.

07:40.720 --> 07:41.909
I do have a job.

07:41.910 --> 07:43.590
And I took a day off from that job

07:43.600 --> 07:44.909
to do an even more important job...

07:44.910 --> 07:46.674
to connect with my daughter.

07:46.675 --> 07:48.549
In your face.

07:48.550 --> 07:51.410
I will not have that in my face again.

07:52.514 --> 07:54.989
All right, let's get
this field trip started

07:54.990 --> 07:57.119
with a little bus song.

07:57.120 --> 07:58.679
♪ Hey, Mickey, you're so fine ♪

07:58.680 --> 08:00.029
♪ You're so fine, you blow my mind ♪

08:00.030 --> 08:01.220
♪ Hey, Mickey ♪

08:01.250 --> 08:02.270
♪ Hey, Mickey ♪

08:02.290 --> 08:03.299
Come on, Anna-Kat!

08:03.300 --> 08:04.692
What are you doing?

08:04.693 --> 08:07.069
What is a bus ride without a sing-along?

08:07.070 --> 08:08.329
Come on, everybody!

08:08.330 --> 08:09.339
♪ Hey, Mickey, you're so... ♪

08:09.340 --> 08:10.879
♪ Oh, Mickey, you're so fine ♪

08:10.880 --> 08:12.219
♪ You're the finest in my mind ♪

08:12.220 --> 08:13.539
♪ Hey, Mickey ♪

08:13.540 --> 08:14.840
Hey, Mickey!

08:14.860 --> 08:17.830
Dude! What are you doing?

08:17.831 --> 08:20.549
Mom always said to dance like
no one's watching and...

08:20.550 --> 08:22.044
to sleep like nobody's watching.

08:23.211 --> 08:24.219
I had trouble sleeping.

08:24.220 --> 08:25.919
I thought people were watching me.

08:25.920 --> 08:28.679
Sorry. Ablin ruined everything.

08:28.680 --> 08:30.119
Yeah.

08:30.120 --> 08:31.759
Mother always said that, too.

08:35.265 --> 08:36.890
The smoothie plan worked perfectly.

08:36.892 --> 08:38.799
Sometimes I think about
using my powers for good,

08:38.799 --> 08:40.899
and then I do stuff like
this and I think...

08:40.900 --> 08:42.129
Nah.

08:42.130 --> 08:44.739
So, you drank expired yogurt
and it didn't make you sick?

08:44.740 --> 08:45.770
How'd you pull that off?

08:45.776 --> 08:47.276
It wasn't really expired.

08:47.277 --> 08:48.487
So how'd you get sick?

08:48.488 --> 08:49.500
We faked it.

08:52.866 --> 08:55.743
You don't need to understand
the plan for it to work.

08:55.744 --> 08:56.749
Oh, thank God.

08:56.750 --> 08:58.496
Cooper, how'd you get
out of school today?

08:58.497 --> 09:01.089
Oh, I don't really have to
worry about stuff like that.

09:01.090 --> 09:04.589
_

09:05.900 --> 09:06.921
You get a boat!

09:06.922 --> 09:08.256
And you get a boat!

09:08.270 --> 09:09.999
And you get a boat!

09:14.971 --> 09:16.430
Oh, no. Dad's home.

09:16.431 --> 09:18.057
He's supposed to be on
Anna-Kat's field trip!

09:18.058 --> 09:20.142
- Guys, go hide.
- Why? Then I won't get to see your dad.

09:20.143 --> 09:21.150
That's the point.

09:22.896 --> 09:25.609
You don't need to understand
the plan for it to work.

09:25.610 --> 09:27.340
Let's vámanos, compadre.

09:27.818 --> 09:30.319
Come on. We got to make
ourselves look sick again.

09:39.955 --> 09:42.439
Hey, guys. I'm not going on
Anna-Kat's field trip anymore,

09:42.440 --> 09:43.959
so I came home to see how you're doing.

09:43.960 --> 09:45.629
I still feel sick.

09:45.630 --> 09:48.170
I feel like Taylor reads... terrible.

09:48.171 --> 09:49.959
Oh, no. Sounds like
you're getting worse.

09:49.960 --> 09:51.500
I better stay here and
take care of you guys.

09:51.508 --> 09:54.209
Y-You shouldn't stay home
just because we're sick.

09:54.210 --> 09:56.579
Why not grab some quality Greg time?

09:56.580 --> 09:58.179
Yeah, go catch a movie.

09:58.180 --> 10:00.379
There's two Ruth Bader
Ginsburg films out.

10:00.380 --> 10:02.609
She's your celebrity hall
pass, for God's sake.

10:02.610 --> 10:04.279
I'm happy to take care of you two.

10:04.280 --> 10:06.559
I'm gonna make you some of my
mother's famous chicken soup.

10:06.560 --> 10:08.060
Do you know what the
secret ingredient is?

10:08.066 --> 10:09.442
- Is it love?
- Love?

10:10.040 --> 10:12.319
No. It's...

10:12.320 --> 10:14.320
I don't want to tell you anymore.

10:16.741 --> 10:18.599
Ugh. Now instead of ditch day,

10:18.600 --> 10:20.999
we have to stay home and
pretend to be sick.

10:21.000 --> 10:23.470
Yeah, I know. I was here, too.

10:26.740 --> 10:29.039
Don't wander off. Stay together.

10:29.040 --> 10:30.679
Don't climb on that!

10:32.007 --> 10:34.609
Caldwell Farms is a fully functional

10:34.610 --> 10:36.635
fruit and animal farm.

10:36.636 --> 10:38.721
But not an "Animal Farm"

10:38.722 --> 10:41.949
like George Orwell's allegorical novella

10:41.950 --> 10:45.853
that criticized the rhetoric
of the Russian Revolution.

10:47.990 --> 10:50.232
Always funny. Always.

10:50.233 --> 10:52.499
I'm also proud to point out

10:52.500 --> 10:55.799
Caldwell Farms' newest edition...

10:55.800 --> 10:58.539
this gorgeous gazebo

10:58.540 --> 11:01.599
built by none other than
your Principal Ablin.

11:02.610 --> 11:03.679
Wow!

11:03.680 --> 11:05.497
Why would you build them a gazebo?

11:05.498 --> 11:06.679
Because I love it here,

11:06.680 --> 11:08.579
and I hope to be buried
under it someday.

11:08.580 --> 11:10.252
So in your face.

11:10.253 --> 11:12.119
Well, my face is a shield,

11:12.120 --> 11:14.249
so it bounces off and hits
your face twice as hard!

11:14.250 --> 11:15.382
Double face!

11:15.383 --> 11:16.759
Double face?

11:16.760 --> 11:18.459
That's the worst of all faces.

11:18.460 --> 11:21.759
Uh, now, before we move
on to the petting zoo,

11:21.760 --> 11:23.474
does anyone have any questions?

11:23.475 --> 11:25.530
Yes.

11:26.600 --> 11:29.189
What are those things behind you?

11:30.070 --> 11:32.100
Uh...

11:32.110 --> 11:33.525
You mean the apples?

11:33.526 --> 11:35.569
Ooh! Apples!

11:35.570 --> 11:37.639
Very interesting.

11:37.640 --> 11:39.199
What do they do?

11:39.960 --> 11:42.009
They just...

11:42.010 --> 11:43.279
They're apples!

11:43.280 --> 11:45.319
Mom, no. Don't play First Day on Earth.

11:45.320 --> 11:46.740
Let's just go to the petting zoo.

11:46.748 --> 11:48.019
One second.

11:48.020 --> 11:50.650
Gerald, so, these apples,

11:50.660 --> 11:53.003
where are their parents?

11:53.004 --> 11:55.629
Well, I suppose...

11:55.630 --> 11:57.859
in a way, that's me.

11:57.860 --> 12:00.136
Mom, please stop!

12:00.880 --> 12:03.389
Does your mom really not
know what apples are?

12:03.390 --> 12:04.959
She's just playing this dumb game

12:04.960 --> 12:06.399
that she thinks is funny

12:06.400 --> 12:10.146
but is definitely not funny.

12:13.108 --> 12:15.401
Anna-Kat, what is wrong?!

12:15.402 --> 12:16.479
Katie?

12:16.480 --> 12:18.510
See, you eat it.

12:19.990 --> 12:22.449
I know what a damn apple is, Ablin.

12:22.450 --> 12:24.109
You are gonna be buried
under that gazebo

12:24.110 --> 12:25.160
sooner than you think.

12:27.290 --> 12:28.330
Excuse me.

12:29.791 --> 12:32.219
I just got off the phone
with an old college friend

12:32.220 --> 12:34.429
who works in infectious
diseases at the Mayo Clinic.

12:34.430 --> 12:35.859
He said that food poisoning

12:35.860 --> 12:37.506
from dairy products is very serious.

12:37.507 --> 12:38.769
I think it's out of our systems.

12:38.770 --> 12:39.839
It's not.

12:39.840 --> 12:41.009
But it will be.

12:41.010 --> 12:42.699
My friend gave very
specific instructions

12:42.700 --> 12:44.596
on how to flush the
toxins from your bodies.

12:44.597 --> 12:46.473
We're gonna sweat it out.

12:51.020 --> 12:52.856
How long do we have to
stay in here like this?

12:52.857 --> 12:54.679
- Just an hour.
- An hour?!

12:54.680 --> 12:57.401
No way! I look like I've
been Chaka Khanned!

12:57.402 --> 12:58.610
You know who Chaka Khan is?

12:58.611 --> 13:00.889
Oh. That's a person?

13:00.890 --> 13:02.531
I thought it meant being electrocuted.

13:02.532 --> 13:04.890
Stay here. I'll be back to
check on you in an hour.

13:06.930 --> 13:08.299
This sucks!

13:08.300 --> 13:10.159
I hate being sick!

13:10.160 --> 13:11.180
You're not really sick.

13:11.200 --> 13:12.790
Oh, yeah.

13:16.296 --> 13:18.005
- Hey. How's the trip going?
- Terrible.

13:18.006 --> 13:20.909
I need the nice parent's
perspective on the situation.

13:20.910 --> 13:23.439
I have been trying to have
fun with Anna-Kat all day,

13:23.440 --> 13:24.849
but she keeps shutting me down.

13:24.850 --> 13:26.689
I've been doing our greatest hits...

13:26.690 --> 13:28.849
sang songs, First Day on Earth.

13:28.850 --> 13:31.310
Maybe you're trying too
hard. Just be yourself.

13:31.311 --> 13:33.520
If I were myself, I wouldn't
be on this field trip.

13:33.521 --> 13:35.229
It's Anna-Kat. You
know what she likes...

13:35.230 --> 13:37.159
true crime fiction, the
wrath of Mother Nature,

13:37.160 --> 13:39.652
YouTube videos of sleeping
bears falling out of trees.

13:40.630 --> 13:42.460
And ponies.

13:42.470 --> 13:44.899
Maybe I'm not trying too hard,

13:44.900 --> 13:47.659
but, actually, I'm not
trying hard enough.

13:47.660 --> 13:49.244
So the opposite of what I just said?

13:49.245 --> 13:50.919
I use you as a sounding board, Greg.

13:50.920 --> 13:52.680
I don't come to you for answers.

13:53.340 --> 13:55.409
I'll give you a Jolly Rancher

13:55.410 --> 13:57.550
if you help me bond with my kid.

13:58.600 --> 14:00.630
You're mine now.

14:04.720 --> 14:06.059
Now, step two.

14:06.060 --> 14:08.055
You need to put this all
over your faces and bodies.

14:08.056 --> 14:09.629
- What is that?
- It's a homemade salve

14:09.630 --> 14:11.266
of mustard, turmeric, and garlic.

14:11.267 --> 14:12.759
Now that the toxins are out,

14:12.760 --> 14:14.853
you need to put this in
your pores immediately.

14:14.854 --> 14:16.981
That's not necessary, Dad.
We're feeling much better.

14:16.982 --> 14:19.219
Do you guys know what
alkaline-hepatitis-12 is?

14:19.220 --> 14:20.619
- No.
- Well, you can get it

14:20.620 --> 14:21.629
if you don't do this.

14:29.702 --> 14:32.037
When you're done putting it
on, get back in the bathroom.

14:33.250 --> 14:35.082
Okay, now you have to let the heat

14:35.083 --> 14:36.439
melt it into your pores.

14:36.440 --> 14:37.584
I'll be back in an hour.

14:42.966 --> 14:44.258
We're missing a lot of fun.

14:44.259 --> 14:45.635
Pictures can be deceiving.

14:45.636 --> 14:46.859
There's a video.

14:46.860 --> 14:48.679
This is the best time of my life!

14:48.680 --> 14:50.339
It's just one person.

14:50.340 --> 14:52.569
We're all having the
best time of our lives!

14:57.105 --> 14:59.439
Hey, Anna-Kat, look who I just found!

14:59.440 --> 15:01.609
It is Major Cuddles!

15:01.610 --> 15:04.269
And he has come to life!

15:04.270 --> 15:05.460
Mom, no.

15:05.470 --> 15:07.649
Playing with toy ponies is one thing,

15:07.650 --> 15:10.659
but playing with real-life ponies

15:10.660 --> 15:12.077
is even better.

15:12.078 --> 15:14.190
You still play with toy ponies?

15:14.860 --> 15:16.089
No.

15:16.090 --> 15:17.833
Ponies are for babies.

15:17.834 --> 15:19.585
Ohh! Mrs. Otto.

15:19.586 --> 15:22.329
Please put Beverly back!

15:22.330 --> 15:23.769
She spooks easily

15:23.770 --> 15:26.133
a-and needs the structure of her corral.

15:26.134 --> 15:27.539
I don't know who Beverly is.

15:27.540 --> 15:28.960
This is Major Cuddles.

15:29.620 --> 15:32.890
Do you and your friends
want to pet Major Cuddles?

15:35.510 --> 15:37.603
Can you stop? Please.

15:37.604 --> 15:38.849
Come on, Anna-Kat.

15:38.850 --> 15:40.772
I took the day off to hang out with you.

15:40.773 --> 15:42.232
Can we talk about this later?

15:42.233 --> 15:43.525
Why can't we talk about it now?

15:43.526 --> 15:45.360
Because you're ruining the field trip.

15:45.361 --> 15:47.329
I am not ruining the field trip.

15:47.330 --> 15:48.822
Am I, Major Cuddles?

15:54.871 --> 15:56.205
My gazebo!

15:56.206 --> 15:57.539
Beverly!

15:58.670 --> 16:01.711
Okay. Now I'm ruining the field trip.

16:02.700 --> 16:05.439
Beverly! Come back here, girl!

16:05.440 --> 16:07.299
Beverly, please come home!

16:07.300 --> 16:10.039
Maybe all of this
yelling is scaring her.

16:10.040 --> 16:11.500
We should ease up for a sec.

16:11.510 --> 16:13.879
That's good advice for you, too.

16:13.880 --> 16:16.579
Hey! That is not fair.

16:16.580 --> 16:19.039
You know, the only reason that
I came on this field trip

16:19.040 --> 16:21.689
was because I felt bad
about working a lot lately

16:21.690 --> 16:23.440
and not spending enough time with you.

16:23.441 --> 16:25.567
You're just trying to
force having fun with me.

16:25.568 --> 16:27.159
It is not forced.

16:27.160 --> 16:29.629
I am just trying to connect
by doing things you like.

16:29.630 --> 16:32.469
First Day on Earth, singing "Mickey"...

16:32.470 --> 16:34.179
I don't like those things anymore.

16:34.180 --> 16:35.990
Well, what about ponies?

16:35.995 --> 16:38.330
You were just playing with
your ponies yesterday at home.

16:38.331 --> 16:40.039
Yeah... at home.

16:40.040 --> 16:43.679
I don't need my friends knowing
I still play with ponies.

16:43.680 --> 16:46.047
Can't you see how that can
be embarrassing for me?

16:48.620 --> 16:49.967
Yeah.

16:49.968 --> 16:52.719
Mom, I've changed. I like
different stuff now.

16:52.720 --> 16:53.790
I have new friends,

16:53.800 --> 16:55.720
and I just want to be
like everyone else.

16:58.790 --> 17:01.399
It's almost time to go.

17:01.400 --> 17:03.199
I'm gonna go get on the bus.

17:11.609 --> 17:13.309
Well, we found Beverly.

17:13.310 --> 17:14.608
She's back in her corral,

17:14.609 --> 17:16.367
sleeping under four weighted blankets.

17:16.368 --> 17:20.749
Man. I blinked for a second,
and she changed on me.

17:20.750 --> 17:23.079
No matter how many times it happens,

17:23.079 --> 17:24.960
I'm never ready for it.

17:24.961 --> 17:26.618
I know what you mean.

17:26.619 --> 17:29.259
I wasn't ready to lose my gazebo, but...

17:29.260 --> 17:30.299
here I am.

17:33.390 --> 17:35.529
I'll get you for this, Katie Otto.

17:38.099 --> 17:40.726
Okay, that's enough of that.

17:40.727 --> 17:42.686
Get me in the shower immediately!

17:42.687 --> 17:44.646
Hang on. There's one last
thing you need to do.

17:44.647 --> 17:45.779
Put these in your ears.

17:45.780 --> 17:47.190
You have to be joking.

17:47.191 --> 17:48.450
I know, but in most of the world,

17:48.460 --> 17:50.620
onions are used to treat
all sorts of illnesses.

17:50.630 --> 17:52.990
This is quick... five minutes,
and then you're totally done.

17:53.580 --> 17:55.241
What do the scallions do?

17:55.242 --> 17:57.920
They make you look more ridiculous.

17:57.930 --> 17:58.950
What are you doing?

17:58.953 --> 18:00.519
After your mother threw
me off the school bus,

18:00.520 --> 18:01.759
I came home to check on you guys.

18:01.760 --> 18:03.299
I quickly found Trip and Cooper,

18:03.300 --> 18:05.751
who are for sure the worst
hiders in the world.

18:18.097 --> 18:19.859
When I asked them what
they were doing there,

18:19.860 --> 18:23.519
Cooper started giving me what
was clearly an elaborate lie.

18:23.520 --> 18:25.279
I made it clear unless
he told me the truth,

18:25.280 --> 18:27.106
I'd tell your mother everything.

18:27.720 --> 18:30.120
He immediately spilled his guts.

18:31.820 --> 18:33.403
When I asked Trip to confirm the story,

18:33.404 --> 18:36.459
he said he couldn't because he
didn't know what was going on.

18:36.460 --> 18:38.992
If you guys ever lie to me again,

18:38.993 --> 18:40.919
I will post this picture everywhere

18:40.920 --> 18:42.519
so all your friends see it.

18:42.520 --> 18:44.623
I'll post it at the school
library, at Izzo's Hardware...

18:44.624 --> 18:46.619
It would just be easier to
post it on the Internet.

18:46.620 --> 18:47.870
Why are you helping him?

18:48.600 --> 18:50.340
That was really messed up, Dad.

18:50.350 --> 18:51.838
I thought you were the nice parent.

18:51.839 --> 18:53.790
I am nice, but you took advantage of me,

18:53.800 --> 18:56.079
so the lesson is, never
piss off the nice parent,

18:56.080 --> 18:58.470
because if you do, you get
punished 10 times harder.

18:58.471 --> 18:59.519
You'll also be happy to know

18:59.520 --> 19:00.810
the stuff you rubbed all over yourself

19:00.820 --> 19:02.680
turned out to be a darn
good salad dressing.

19:02.684 --> 19:04.602
Yeah, that really turns my day around.

19:14.300 --> 19:15.890
♪ Oh, Mickey, you're so fine ♪

19:15.900 --> 19:17.159
♪ You're so fine, you blow my mind ♪

19:17.160 --> 19:18.670
♪ Hey, Mickey ♪

19:18.690 --> 19:20.599
♪ Hey, Mickey ♪

19:20.600 --> 19:22.240
♪ Oh, Mickey, you're so fine ♪

19:22.250 --> 19:23.599
♪ You're so fine, you blow my mind ♪

19:23.600 --> 19:25.120
♪ Hey, Mickey ♪

19:25.140 --> 19:27.370
♪ Hey, Mickey ♪

19:29.810 --> 19:33.049
♪ Oh, Mickey, what a pity,
you don't understand ♪

19:33.050 --> 19:36.460
♪ You take me by the heart
when you take me by the hand ♪

19:36.470 --> 19:39.429
♪ Oh, Mickey, you're so pretty,
you don't understand ♪

19:39.430 --> 19:41.859
It's guys like you, Mickey!

19:41.860 --> 19:44.766
♪ Oh, what you do, Mickey, do, Mickey ♪

19:44.767 --> 19:47.230
♪ Don't break my heart, Mickey ♪

19:48.900 --> 19:50.981
Thanks for throwing me a bone.

19:50.982 --> 19:52.169
No problem.

19:52.170 --> 19:54.469
And if you want to chaperone
another field trip,

19:54.470 --> 19:55.999
- if you behave...
- Mm-hmm.

19:56.000 --> 19:57.028
... I'd be okay with that.

19:57.029 --> 19:59.509
That is so sweet.

19:59.510 --> 20:02.367
But I've been banned
from all field trips.

20:02.368 --> 20:03.952
Was that the point of the whole day?

20:03.953 --> 20:07.957
No. Just an awesome bonus.

20:10.020 --> 20:11.770
♪ Oh, Mickey, you're so fine ♪

20:11.780 --> 20:13.189
♪ You're so fine, you blow my mind ♪

20:13.190 --> 20:14.600
♪ Hey, Mickey ♪

20:14.630 --> 20:16.132
♪ Hey, Mickey ♪

20:16.980 --> 20:18.599
They totally fell for it.

20:20.710 --> 20:22.137
You're a real hard-ass today.

20:22.138 --> 20:23.221
I know. It was really fun.

20:23.222 --> 20:25.149
What is going on around here?

20:25.150 --> 20:26.249
You're mean.

20:26.250 --> 20:28.979
Anna-Kat has become a
normal kid with friends.

20:28.980 --> 20:30.479
Wait, let me check something.

20:30.480 --> 20:32.619
Taylor, how you doing, honey?

20:32.620 --> 20:34.899
Good! Doing homework! Love you so much!

20:34.900 --> 20:37.789
I have no idea what's going on anymore.

20:42.260 --> 20:44.229
That's weird. There's nobody here.

20:44.230 --> 20:46.160
Hmm.

20:47.740 --> 20:49.649
In your face!

